description:
Going off of the field guide 'Dragonflies and Damselfies of the East' pp.106, I think this is a male Stream Bluet. Identifying marks include:
* Joined postocular spot (blue 'dumbbell' shape on the back of the head)
* Blue/turquose eyes with black cap (the greenish part of the eyes are more visible in the last picture)
* Antehumeral stripe is narrower than the humeral stripe (blue stripes on the thorax surrounding the median (center) stripe, and outer black stripes next to them, respectively)
* Black 'V' shape on S8 (near the end of the abdomen)

I think that rules out the most similar-looking species - Azure, Skimming, and Turquoise Bluets.

description:
I spent about a half hour trying to get pictures of this guy. Eventually, while distracted by a female, he flew straight into the side of a dock, bonked his noggin, and fell into the water.

I scooped him out and he seemed a bit dazed for awhile, and I was able to finally get a few decent pictures. Afterward, he just sat on my finger for a few more minutes, started beating his wings in place for awhile (I'm not sure why), and finally flew away.

It was really neat! Well worth the wait.
